amily:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> hosting Daphne Jackson </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">fellowships</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">43% of Daphne Jackson Fellowships are sponsored by the UK’s Research Councils</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The Daphne Jackson Trust recommends that the government supports more flexible working opportunities for researchers, such as the part-time fe</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">llowships offered by the Daphne Jackson Trust </span></li></ul><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:normal">Daphne Jackson Fellowships </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:normal">–</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:normal"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:normal">an example of good practice </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:normal">in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:normal"> retaining talented women in STEM careers</span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">In the fast moving world of scientific research, highly qualified and skilled individuals who temporarily </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">step back from research, quickly find themselves lagging behind their peers. And when they</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> want to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> return to work, they struggle to find research-based employment which fully utilises their knowledge and experience. </span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">In particular, women who are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> equally</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> ta</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">lented, motivated and committed to research</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> as their male peers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">often </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">find themselves taking a career break to bring up young children. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">In</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> most cases, this break comes at a time when both the individual </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">concerned, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">and their sp</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">onsors, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">have invested a signi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">ficant amount of time and money developing the skills and knowledge required to become expert in their chosen discipline.   </span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">The Daphne Ja</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">ckson Trust was founded in 1992, following the death of Daphne Jackson, the UK’s first female Professor of Physics. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">e Trust offers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> flexible, part-time, paid fellowships, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">to help</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> scientists, technologists, engineers and mathematicians (STEM) return to their careers after a break of two or more years.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">&#xa0;</span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Fellows carry out their research within UK universities and industrial research institutions, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">he Trust provides the infrastructure and expertise required to recruit, select, and re-train fellows and administer the awards,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> whilst the host institution cover</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">s overheads and consumable costs, and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> salary support is provided by external sponsors such as the UK research councils, universities, charities, learned societies and industrial partners. Many universities both sponsor and host fellows.</span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">The UK’s scientific</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> research community </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">is taking</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> proactive measures to remove barriers that prevent a diverse range of talented professionals succeeding in scientific and engineering careers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> This includes offering flexible working hours, providing on-site, affordable childc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">are facilities and in general developing a working culture in which the value of a reasonable work-life balance is recognised by staff at all levels.</span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">One of the factors contributing to the decline in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> numbers of women in STEM academic careers further up the career ladder, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">is undoubtedly </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">that a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> significant number of very well qualified and highly trained women have a career break and do not return. </span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Women ofte</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">n do not plan a career break.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">They may</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> have</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> children</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> and expect to return to work following maternity leave. But </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">many</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> find that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> having a family is coupled with</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> relocation with a partner</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">the planned maternity leave extends into</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> a longer career break.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">In other instances, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">women may have to deal </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">with unexpected illness, or caring responsibilities for older relatives.</span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">8</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Once on a career break there are few opportunities for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> to return to research at the level commensurate with their skills and experience without help from a returners scheme such</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> as the Daphne Jackson F</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">ellowship scheme</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">.  </span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">9</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">The Trust</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">’s </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">fellowships </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">help retain a talented and diverse STEM workforce, and prevent a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> large pool of talented women </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">being</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> lost to the STEM academic sector</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">. The two-year fellowship offers </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">returners</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> the opportunity to balance an individually tailored retraining programme with a challenging research project in a suitably supportive environment.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> </span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">10</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Seven out of ten fellows stay in research for at least 2 years after successfully completing their fellowsh</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">ip, and many go on to permanent research posts within universities and in industry. Four of the UK’s female professors returned to research with a Daphne Jackson Fellowship, following a career break.</span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">11</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Daphne Jackson Trust Fellowships are an example of good </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">practice, showing how successful returning to a STEM research career can be</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">(see feedback from fellows </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">paragraphs 27-32</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">).</span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">12</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">The committee has asked what universities and the higher education sector can do to retain graduates and PhD students in academic care</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">ers and our answer would be that it is not simply about retaining</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> - </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">the sector needs to offer a way for qualified and skilled women to return if they have left the sector.</span></h1><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /></p><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:normal">The Daphne Jackson Trust - </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:normal">Facts and figures</span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">13</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">The Daphne Jackson Trust aims to:</span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 57.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Return researchers to their careers with confidence</span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 57.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Helps retain a talented STEM workforce by offering flexible fellowships with mentoring and training to allow women and men to return to research after a career break</span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 57.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Supports equality and diversity in the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> research workforce</span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 57.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Develops partnerships that extend the reach and increase the impact of flexible working opportunities for STEM researchers</span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">14</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Although the Daphne Jackson Trusts supports women and men who have taken a career break of two or more years for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">family, caring or health reasons, 9</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">5</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">% of Daphne Jackson Trust fellows are women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">.</span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">15</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">The Trus</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">t has to date, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">awarded 250 fellowships and there are currently 35 fellows in post</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> in UK universities and research establishments.</span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">16</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">The length of the career break </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">an ind</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">ividual has taken before approaching the Daphne Jackson Trust can vary</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> between 2 and 20 years, b</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">ut </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">the typical length of break that we deal with is 4-8 years.</span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">17</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Seven out of ten </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Daphne Jackson </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">fellows stay in research for at least 2 years after successfully </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">complet</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">ing their fellowship and many go on to permanent research posts within universities and in industry.</span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">18</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Four of the UK’s female professors returned to research</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> with a Daphne Jackson Fellowship,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> following a career break</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">.</span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">19</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">The Trust supports women who have a PhD and/or at least three years research experience. </span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">20</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">43% Daphne Jackson Fel</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">lowships are sponsored by the UK</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">’s research councils (MRC, NERC, EPSRC, BBSRC and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">STFC</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">).</span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">21</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">In 2011 the Trust </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">appointed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> a new Chief Executive and s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">ince then there have been significant changes and improvements to the organisation.  The governance has increased expertise, there have been improvements to efficiency and effectiveness in the application processes and staffing structure</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">.  </span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">22</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">The Trust has b</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">een proactively seeking out new opportunities to increase the numbers of women it can help and new organisations with whom to develop partnerships.  Sponsored fellowships have been developed to meet the needs of sponsoring organisations wishing to engage w</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">ith the Trust and the fellowships.  </span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">23</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Sponsored fellowships allow a university to make an agreement to sponsor a fellowship and then the opportunity is advertised and the sponsor may choose the most appropriate applicant, who will then proceed through the T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">rust’s application process.  </span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">24</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Many universities are recognising the need to engage with returners as a pool of untapped talent and the sponsored fellowship model allows them to do so. They are able to choose the best applicant </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">to meet their strategic prior</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">ities,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> whilst working with the Trust and using our expertise in dealing with returners. </span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">25</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">The Trust’s application process offers an unrivalled level of support, guidance mentoring and advice to applicants and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">then </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">fellows</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">. This is undoubtedly why our fellows are so successful in returning to careers. </span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">26</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">In the last 18 months the Trust has made new sponsored fellowship agreements with 16 universities. </span><a name="_GoBack"></a></h1><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Feedback from Daphne Jackson Fellows</span></p><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">27</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">‘I have recently been awarded a Da</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">phne Jackson Fellowship and am very excited about the opportunity it has given me. Until I discovered the Daphne Jackson Trust, I had begun to think that I would never have the chance to return to the research I love. Having been out of my research field f</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">or a considerable time, I was aware that career breaks and part-time working had left holes in my CV and that other fellowship schemes did not seem to be able to see past these. </span></h1><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">From the start, the Daphne Jackson application process considered these break</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">s and seemed to look beyond them. I had a constructive phone interview where the impact of my career breaks together with the training needs I had, were thoroughly discussed. Far from feeling these were insurmountable barriers, I began to feel that, just p</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">ossibly, here was a scheme that could help me to overcome them. </span></h1><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 21.6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In the short time since I was awarded the fellowship, opportunities are appearing. I have given an invited talk and discussed potential collaborations with several researchers. This is the break I was hoping for and it would not have been possible without </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the Daphne Jackson Trust and their wise and supportive team.’ Dr Tamsin Majerus, DJT Fellow sponsored by</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> NERC and University of Nottingham.</span></p><h1 style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 43.2pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">28</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">‘I am a Scientific Investigator at </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">GlaxoSmithKline a large pharma</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">ce</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight